# 🍽️ Restaurant Data Analysis – Level 2

This section builds on the previous tasks by exploring more complex relationships in the restaurant dataset. The focus is on cuisine patterns, location-based insights, and brand-level analysis.

## ✅ Completed Tasks

### 🔹 Task 5: Cuisine Combination
- Found the most common combinations of cuisines served together in restaurants.
- Explored whether specific cuisine combos tend to have better ratings than others.

### 🔹 Task 6: Geographic Analysis
- Mapped restaurant locations using their latitude and longitude.
- Identified dense clusters and location-based trends in specific areas.

### 🔹 Task 7: Restaurant Chains
- Detected restaurant chains operating in multiple locations.
- Analyzed average ratings and popularity (votes) of each chain.

### 🔹 Task 8: Top Cuisines
- Determined the top three most common cuisines in the dataset.
- Calculated the percentage of restaurants offering each top cuisine.

## 🛠️ Tools & Libraries Used
- Python 🐍
- Pandas 📊
- Matplotlib & Seaborn 📈
- Plotly / Folium (for maps) 🗺️

## 📄 Dataset Overview
- Includes data on:
  - City and location coordinates
  - Cuisines offered
  - Ratings and votes
  - Delivery options and price range

